1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Acadiana Legislative Delegation student worker Ty Hebert on the occasion of
3 his graduation from Louisiana State University.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Ty Hebert for his service to the Acadiana
5 Legislative Delegation and to commend him on the occasion of his graduation from
6 Louisiana State University; and
7 WHEREAS, Ty is graduating with a bachelor of science degree in agricultural
8 business from Louisiana State University on May 15, 2026; and
9 WHEREAS, Ty is a member of Kappa Sigma and served as fraternity president from
10 November 2024 to November 2025; he was nominated for Interfraternity Conference
11 President of the Year for his service; and
12 WHEREAS, Ty led a fundraiser that raised over fifty thousand dollars for the
13 military heroes campaign that benefits wounded United States Navy SEALs; he also hosted
14 a leadership development workshop to benefit youth in agriculture; and
15 WHEREAS, Ty is a native of Cow Island, Louisiana, and served as president of the
16 American Junior Brahman Association during his freshman year; and
17 WHEREAS, Ty has displayed an outstanding work ethic, attention to detail, and
18 willingness to take on a wide range of responsibilities during his time with the Acadiana
19 Legislative Delegation, which began on November 26, 2023; and
