1 WHEREAS, Ty has supported community engagement efforts, including assisting
2 with a successful crawfish boil, and contributed to the review and development of detailed
3 legislation; he has also made a concerted effort to build and maintain positive working
4 relationships within the delegation office and fostered a collaborative and supportive
5 environment; and
6 WHEREAS, in addition to his service at the Louisiana State Capitol, Ty interned
7 with United States House Speaker Mike Johnson in Washington, D.C., in 2024; and
8 WHEREAS, Ty Hebert is deserving of recognition for his initiative, reliability,
9 ability to balance administrative and substantive work, and service with the Acadiana
10 Legislative Delegation.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
12 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Acadiana Legislative Delegation student
13 worker Ty Hebert on the occasion of his graduation from Louisiana State University and
14 does hereby express enduring appreciation for his outstanding service to the delegation and
15 its members.
